# requires: v0.14
#
# v0.14 str ↔ list[byte] bridge round-trip:
#   - s.len()           — byte count (v0.14 semantics; was rune count
#                         pre-v0.14, dead-code path since typeck rejected
#                         str entirely)
#   - s.bytes()         — fresh list[byte] copy of s's bytes
#   - buf.to_str()      — fresh str from a byte buffer
#
# Asserts the round-trip preserves byte content and that print over the
# new str produces identical output. The corpus runner exercises both
# `zerg run` (interpreter) and `zerg build` (cc compile + execute), so
# this fixture pins parity across both halves.

s := "hello"
print s.len()
buf := s.bytes()
print buf.len()
back := buf.to_str()
print back
